The paper proposes a novel probabilistic model for visual question answering, which involves learning embeddings for images, questions, and answers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves learning the best parameterization of embeddings, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves large-scale optimization techniques and transfer learning, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
